The paper is about biomedical image segmentation using a novel architecture called ACE-net. The paper focuses on enhancing the feature representation and utilization by augmenting the contracting and expansive paths. This is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also introduces advanced techniques such as ASPP, dense connection, and deep supervision mechanisms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper deals with biomedical images, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which is a subfield of neural engineering (cs.NE) research.
